title: The mystery of hanging coffins: Are modern Bo people the genetic heirs of an ancient burial tradition?
description: A new study has uncovered a direct genetic link between ancient practitioners of the Hanging Coffin burial tradition and the modern Bo people in Southwest China. The findings published in Nature Communications offer unprecedented insight into the deep ancestral origins and migratory history associated with this unique mortuary practice.
